00:26:22.815 --> 00:26:26.260
it's "The lilies of the
field, they do not toil,

00:26:26.260 --> 00:26:27.640
nor do they sow."

00:26:27.640 --> 00:26:29.000
They don't do anything.

00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:32.610
Actually, if you're a lily,
you are busting your empennage

00:26:32.610 --> 00:26:34.640
to make flowers.

00:26:34.640 --> 00:26:39.980
All the energy you put into
making ova, eggs and pollen,

00:26:39.980 --> 00:26:41.550
it's a tremendous
amount of work.

00:26:41.550 --> 00:26:44.030
And the reason it's
done, apparently,

00:26:44.030 --> 00:26:46.710
is because of parasites.

00:26:46.710 --> 00:26:50.490
So if you're a meta
multicellular organism,

00:26:50.490 --> 00:26:53.940
like us, your enemy,
in general, is not

00:26:53.940 --> 00:26:56.580
a lion, a tiger, or a bear.

00:26:56.580 --> 00:26:59.310
Those, of course, are trouble,
as well documented in the film.

00:27:02.260 --> 00:27:06.100
But your main problem
is germs and parasites.

00:27:06.100 --> 00:27:13.490
So germs, if they're bacteria,
they're reproducing like crazy.

00:27:13.490 --> 00:27:15.330
They double in just a few hours.

00:27:15.330 --> 00:27:21.030
You'll have-- unchecked--
enormous populations of germs.

00:27:21.030 --> 00:27:23.530
But us, it takes us months.

00:27:23.530 --> 00:27:26.190
And after all the negotiation,
the going out to dinner,

00:27:26.190 --> 00:27:32.180
and all that stuff-- no,
it takes a long time.

00:27:32.180 --> 00:27:36.000
And then, when the kid's born,
you're looking at nothing.

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:39.030
You've got years more
on top of that, right?

00:27:39.030 --> 00:27:43.750
So apparently, sex
is a way to come up

00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:47.350
with a new combination of genes
that the germs, parasites, just

00:27:47.350 --> 00:27:49.940
can't quite keep up with.

00:27:49.940 --> 00:27:53.560
And this is charmingly referred
to as the theory of the Red

00:27:53.560 --> 00:27:55.180
Queen.

00:27:55.180 --> 00:27:57.250
But the guy was British,
so the Red Queen.

00:28:02.520 --> 00:28:04.580
Alice of "Alice
in Wonderland" is

00:28:04.580 --> 00:28:07.170
in "Through the Looking
Glass," the second book.

00:28:07.170 --> 00:28:10.880
And she meets the Red Queen,
who's-- from my understanding,

00:28:10.880 --> 00:28:13.250
Lewis Carroll, I don't
know if he smoked dope,

00:28:13.250 --> 00:28:14.190
but he probably did.

00:28:14.190 --> 00:28:19.760
And so the Red Queen is like
this chess piece person.

00:28:19.760 --> 00:28:22.964
And she's sliding around
on the chessboard of life.

00:28:22.964 --> 00:28:24.380
And so when you're
talking to her,

00:28:24.380 --> 00:28:25.730
you have to run all the time.

00:28:25.730 --> 00:28:29.520
But it's not explained
about the queen's legs

00:28:29.520 --> 00:28:32.482
or her felt bottom,
whatever chess pieces have.

00:28:35.260 --> 00:28:37.630
And so Alice says, "You
know, where I come from,

00:28:37.630 --> 00:28:40.289
if you run all day, you'll
end up somewhere else."

00:28:40.289 --> 00:28:41.830
And the queen says,
"Well, that seems

00:28:41.830 --> 00:28:44.670
like a very slow
sort of country."

00:28:44.670 --> 00:28:48.510
And so this is the
idea of evolution.

00:28:48.510 --> 00:28:51.660
If you stop running, you will
fall off the treadmill of life.

00:28:51.660 --> 00:28:53.210
You will disappear.

00:28:53.210 --> 00:28:55.370
So this having sex, new
combination of genes,

00:28:55.370 --> 00:28:57.920
new combination of genes,
is how you stay in the game.

00:28:57.920 --> 00:29:01.890
And the predictive quality of
the theory of evolution just

00:29:01.890 --> 00:29:02.980
really comes into play.

00:29:02.980 --> 00:29:04.355
And I mentioned
this in Kentucky,

00:29:04.355 --> 00:29:06.640
